-- G7 Statement: Concerned about volatility in yen
-- 
-- Sun Oct 26, 2008 11:54pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/10/27/us-g7-statement-idUSTRE49Q0FJ20081027

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - The Group of Seven (G7) finance ministers and central bank governors said on Monday in a joint statement that they were concerned about recent excessive volatility in the yen's exchange rate. 

 They also said the G7 will continue to monitor markets closely and cooperate as appropriate. G7 also said they have a shared interest in a strong and stable international financial system. (Reporting by  Hideyuki Sano )